We're back with more wellness gua sha tutorials with @wildling_beauty 
Practicing the Facial Gua Sha ritual will clear, smooth, plump, tighten and rejuvenate skin while reducing under-eye circles and puffiness.

1.  Apply Empress Tonic: After cleansing, the Empress Tonic primes skin to absorb face oil. It's an essential step in activating the skin, preparing it for gua sha, and maximizing results. Plant wanters from nutrient-dense sweet fern, damask rose, and Douglas fir stimulate detoxification, promote lymphatic drainage, and hydrate to amplify your gua sha practice.

2.  Apply Empress Oil: This powerful whole plant oil infusion elevates your gua sha ritual by boosting circulation, plumping, and toning the skin. Balm of Gilead and our Resin Nutrient Complex nourish skin and can help stimulate lymphatic flow. Using the Empress Oil in tandem with the Tonic and Stone is what makes our ritual—and results—different from the rest.

3.  Facial Gua Sha With the Empress Stone -- follow along step by step.  This multi-action tool custom-crafted from Bian stone massages our whole plant actives into the skin while manipulating the tissues of the face more precisely than hands alone.

4. You're sure to get the best results when you do the Empress Ritual on the entire face and neck.  It will open up the flow of energy in your entire body. 

Enjoy!

node.title: The 10 Minute Gua Sha Morning Ritual

With immunity at the forefront of health discussions like never before, we’re more than thrilled for beloved L.A. practitioner, Lisa Gainsley of @TheLymphaticMessage to be dropping her first book, THE BOOK OF LYMPH: Self-Care Practices to Enhance Immunity, Health, and Beauty.

To celebrate, we asked Lisa to share this morning routine for lymphatic health with us (get the full story on the homepage). Her practical and easy to follow along advice will get you started if you’re new to the concept and might just provide you with new insights if you’re always practicing a routine…

node.title: The Book Of Lymph: A 5-Step Morning Routine For Lymphatic Health

Grab lunch with Embodiment Coach + Wellness Chef, @bykaraelise We're sharing what folks are making for WFH lunches lately, including this simple, fresh, nutrient-dense falafel bowl to help you put down the laptop for a few and get #backtothebody | #thechalkboardeats #whatsforlunch

Ginger Miso Dressing: 

2 Tbsp miso
2 Tbsp olive oil
1 Tbsp sesame oil
2 Tbsp rice vinegar
1/2 Tbsp coconut aminos or soy sauce 
1 large chunk peeled ginger
Dash of lemon juice
1/2 Tbsp honey
1-2 Tbsp water

Add all of your ingredients into a Vitamix or blender and that’s it!
